The paper deals with the visualization of clustered graphs, which is a topic that falls under the category of graph drawing and visualization (cs.GR). The paper also discusses planarity testing problems, which are related to computational geometry (cs.CG) and algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper involves the study of complexity and NP-completeness, which are topics in theoretical computer science (cs.THE). The use of adjacency matrices and inter-cluster edges suggests that the paper may also be related to graph theory and combinatorics (cs.DM). Finally, the development of a JavaScript library for NodeTrix representations suggests that the paper may also be related to software engineering and human-computer interaction (cs.SI).
